java.lang.invoke

Class MethodType.WeakInternSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.invoke.MethodType.WeakInternSet
  • Enclosing class:
    MethodType

    private static class MethodType.WeakInternSet
extends Object
    Weak intern set based on implementation of the HashSet and WeakHashMap, with weak values. Note: null values will yield NullPointerException Refer to implementation of WeakInternSet for details.
    See Also:
    HashMap, HashSet, WeakHashMap, WeakReference

      • hash

        private static int hash(int h)
        Applies a supplemental hash function to a given hashCode, which defends against poor quality hash functions. This is critical because hashing uses power-of-two length hash tables, that otherwise encounter collisions for hashCodes that do not differ in lower bits.
        Parameters:
        h - preliminary hash code value
        Returns:
        supplemental hash code value

      • get

        MethodType get(MethodType value)
        Returns the entry to which the specified value is mapped, or null if this set contains no entry for the value.

        More formally, if this set contains an entry for value entry to a value value such that entry.equals(value), then this method returns entry; otherwise it returns null.

        Parameters:
        value - value to search for in set
        Returns:
        interned value if in set, otherwise null

      • add

        MethodType add(MethodType value)
        Attempts to add the specified value to the set and returns same value. If the set previously contained an entry for this value, the old value is left untouched and returned as the result.
        Parameters:
        value - value to be added
        Returns:
        the previous entry associated with value, or value if there was no previous entry found

      • resize

        private void resize(int newCapacity)
        Rehashes the contents of this set into a new array with a larger capacity. This method is called automatically when the number of keys in this set reaches its threshold. If current capacity is MAXIMUM_CAPACITY, this method does not resize the set, but sets threshold to Integer.MAX_VALUE. This has the effect of preventing future calls.
        Parameters:
        newCapacity - the new capacity, MUST be a power of two; must be greater than current capacity unless current capacity is MAXIMUM_CAPACITY (in which case value is irrelevant)

        Transfers all entries from src to dest tables
        Parameters:
        src - original table
        dest - new table
